originalText.text: It's generally a nice place. They, usually, do good work on my eye brows (threading). This is my problem with them...they keep changing the hours of operation, plus, now they have this thing where if you need to use their bathroom, they won't let you use it. They keep using the "sink doesn't have water" LIE so nobody can use it. When the other night I was there, after I paid AND tipped them greatly for their services, they didn't let me use the bathroom, and I told them I didn't need water from the sink cuz I have my hand sanitizer, and they still said no, I guess under the impression that I was either going to do something "illegal" or maybe put makeup on my face that they "won't get any money" from doing (example, since I don't tint my eyebrows, they think I'm going to pencil in my eyebrows). They've been on this trip for awhile already. I just left with an attitude!! They also raised their prices. They can be rude at times, as well. They don't know what true customer service is, since they are foreigners with no proper manners (they appear Indian to me). Anyway, pee before you go there. Maybe the toilet doesn't have water either!! ü§£
